20    /**
21    * This class represents a set of discrete points in time.
22    * <br>
23    * It handles the mapping from time indices to time points and back.
24    * It uses a time tick size ("quantum"). This is to make comparison of times safe.
25    * The default tick size is 1.0 / (365.0 * 24.0) (which corresponds to one hour if 1.0 is a non-leap-year):
26    * Times are rounded to the nearest multiple of 1.0 / (365.0 * 24.0).
27    *
28    * This property can be configured via a System.setProperty("net.finmath.functions.TimeDiscretization.timeTickSize").
29    *
30    * Objects of this class are immutable.
31    *
32    * @author Christian Fries
33    * @version 1.6
34    */
